## What Is This App

A mobile-first city companion for Sarajevo. Aggregates events from 30+ local
sources via AI-powered scraping, enriches with bilingual content (Bosnian +
English), presents through mood-driven discovery. Not a dry calendar \u2014 a
curated, atmospheric experience. Answers: "\u0160ta ima ve\u010deras?" and "Gdje da idemo?"

Target users: Sarajevo locals (primary), tourists & expats (secondary).

## Tech Stack

| Layer            | Choice                                    |
|------------------|-------------------------------------------|
| Mobile App       | React Native (Expo) via Natively or Rork          |
| Backend / DB     | Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth + RLS + Edge) |
| Location         | PostGIS (geography type)                  |
| AI Parsing       | OpenAI GPT-4o-mini                        |
| Scraping         | Supabase Edge Functions (Deno) + Apify    |
| Instagram        | Apify Instagram Post Scraper (40 accounts)|
| Auth             | Supabase Auth (Email, Google, Apple)      |
| Maps             | react-native-maps                         |
| Push             | Expo Push Notifications                   |
| Admin Panel      | Next.js                                   |
| Public Site      | Astro or Next.js (SSG for SEO)            |

## Critical Conventions

### Bilingual Everything
- ALL user-facing content: Bosnian (bs) + English (en)
- Fields: title_bs / title_en, description_bs / description_en
- Bosnian = Latin script only (never Cyrillic)
- Diacritics: \u010d, \u0107, \u0161, \u017e, \u0111 \u2014 use `unaccent` extension for search
- Default UI language: Bosnian. English togglable.

### Database Rules
- RLS enabled on ALL tables \u2014 zero exceptions
- UUIDs for primary keys (gen_random_uuid())
- Timestamps: TIMESTAMPTZ in UTC, display in CET/CEST
- Soft deletes via `is_active` boolean \u2014 never hard delete user data
- Denormalized counters where needed (total_checkins, attendance_count)
- PostGIS geography type for location, auto-computed via trigger
- Event series (event_series table) for multi-day festivals & recurring markets

### Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode everywhere
- Functional components + hooks (no class components)
- async/await over .then() chains
- Meaningful error handling \u2014 try/catch with context
- Named exports preferred
- File naming: kebab-case files, PascalCase components
- No `any` types \u2014 define proper interfaces

### Edge Functions (Deno)
- Supabase Edge Functions run Deno, NOT Node.js
- Use supabase-js v2
- Secrets via Deno.env.get('SECRET_NAME')
- Always return structured JSON from scrapers
- Rate limit external APIs, respect robots.txt

### Supabase Patterns
- RPC functions for complex workflows (approve_venue_submission, etc.)
- Service role key ONLY in Edge Functions, NEVER in client code
- Anon key for client-side reads
- Real-time subscriptions for live features (check-ins, stories)

### Git
- Branch: feature/[agent]/[desc] (e.g. feature/scraper/fix-kupikartu)
- Commits: [agent] description (e.g. [backend] add event_series migration)
- PRs reference architecture doc section numbers

